The paper deals with fair allocation of goods, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The algorithmic approach and query complexity analysis suggest that the paper may also belong to sub-categories related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mathematical optimization and game theory concepts may also make it relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
